                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12862800" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 30 Apr 2010 18:42:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I tried reproducing this bug with TestSolrJPerf.java (attached) talking to a stock example solr server on trunk - it ran for over 500M docs without issue.  I stopped it because I need my laptop performance back &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps next I&apos;ll try something that uses multiple threads to add to the client, along with more random pauses on the client side to further exercise the connection establish/release code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12872638" author="hossman" created="Thu, 27 May 2010 22:09:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk updating 240 Solr issues to set the Fix Version to &quot;next&quot; per the process outlined in this email...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-dev/201005.mbox/%3Calpine.DEB.1.10.1005251052040.24672@radix.cryptio.net%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-dev/201005.mbox/%3Calpine.DEB.1.10.1005251052040.24672@radix.cryptio.net%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Selection criteria was &quot;Unresolved&quot; with a Fix Version of 1.5, 1.6, 3.1, or 4.0.  email notifications were suppressed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A unique token for finding these 240 issues in the future: hossversioncleanup20100527&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879527" author="egh" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2010 21:53:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have been reliably encountering this error; however it takes me a day or two to get there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have attached a change which may fix this - I will let you know in day or two. This change ensures that a call is made to method.releaseConnection() for every call to executeMethod(method), &lt;a href=&quot;http://hc.apache.org/httpclient-3.x/threading.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hc.apache.org/httpclient-3.x/threading.html&lt;/a&gt;. The current version of StreamingUpdateSolrServer only calls releaseConnection once for possibly more than one update call (the posts are wrapped in a do...while block).&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12879595" author="egh" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2010 00:37:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW if I am correct this bug was introduced by the use do...while loop added to fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1711&quot; title=&quot;Race condition in org/apache/solr/client/solrj/impl/StreamingUpdateSolrServer.java&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1711&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1711&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879646" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2010 03:02:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good, and just in time for 1.4.1.  Thanks Erik!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
